The page is the oldest interface. Lokta takes one cookbook, sets it with unusual
severity, and asks whether the same grammar holds on a screen and in print.

== Two sources

The structure comes from a film cookbook: a cream stock, a vertical spine, and
rules that stop short of the margin. The warmth comes from a household standard,
the kind of book that lives next to the stove for a generation.

#lk-quote(by: "Siddika Kabir")[
  You do not design a library. You design the quality of an afternoon.
]

== One grammar

Whether the output is a slide, a web view, or this page, the same tokens decide
the surface, the ink, and the single marigold ground that opens a section.
